column1: # Species: Cg - C. glabrata; Sc - S. cerevisiae
# Genotype: wt - wild type strains without any genetic manipulation

# Group: treatment type; MM - Mock treatment as the primary stress and secondary stress; MO - Mock treatment as the primary stress and H2O2 stress as the secondary stress; PM: Phosphate starvation as the primary stress and mock treatment as the secondary stress; PO: phosphate starvation as the primary stress and H2O2 as the secondarys tress
# H2O2: H2O2 stress concentration in mM; Mock - 0mM
# Dilutions: the final dilutions for the culture used for CFU Count
# MO/MM: survival rate on H2O2 stress without the primary stress (calculated from the corresponding MO count)
# PO/PM: survival rate on H2O2 stress with phosphate starvation as the primary stress (calculated from the corresponding PO count)
# Experimenter: the person who did the experiments
